{
  "stem": "14613.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I can-- I can start really-- I can say--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, it's just like certain parts which happen in ghetto-- how we were caught and sent out, I could not remember.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The other parts which, yet, they stay vividly in my mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, if-- when I've told you that we went to school at the beginning of the ghetto in Marysin.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And maybe it's a coincidence, but later on in the ghetto, being there and going to school helped us to survive the winter in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the reason was that most of the homes in the Marysin were wooden homes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what my brother and I used to do, we used to go there, to this Marysin, and take they wood-- pull apart the homes and take the wood and smuggle it in to ghetto.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this way we had some call it coal, wood, to have some heat in our-- in our room.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This got more difficult and more difficult.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we came into an ingenious way of-- of smuggling the wood by building from this wood a very heavy-- we wanted as heavy as possible, because we were interested in the wood-- we were building such, I don't even know how you call it in English, such a thing where you can-- like a frame where you can put old cans of paint, and other-- and things, and you hold it on both sides.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the painters use it to transport some of the cans of paint.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we would build the thing like this, which was very heavy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we would put few-- few cans of paint.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we would go straight to the-- through the guard with this lumber in our hands.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
